<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="321" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1839,2008]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,283,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,283,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Drycothaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently composed of 27 species distributed in the Neotropical region (
<bibRefCitation box="[1128,1277,1840,1864]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" refId="ref5649" refString="Monne, M. A. (2018) Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamilies Lepturinae, Necydalinae, Parandrinae, Prioninae, Spondylidinae, Oxypeltidae, Vesperidae, Disteniidae. Available from: http: // cerambyxcat. com / (accessed 30 March 2018)" type="url">Monné 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="320" refId="ref5744" refString="Tavakilian, G. &amp; Chevillotte, H. (2017) Titan: base de donnees internationales sur les Cerambycidae ou Longicornes. Version 3.0. Available from: http: // titan. gbif. fr / (accessed 30 March 2018)" type="url">Tavakilian &amp; Chevillotte 2017</bibRefCitation>
). When studying the South American species, 
<bibRefCitation box="[950,1269,1876,1901]" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" refId="ref5473" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1990) Notas sobre Calliini. IV. As especies sul-americanas do genero Drycothaea Thomson, 1868. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 34 (3), 607 - 613." type="journal article">Martins &amp; Galileo (1990)</bibRefCitation>
characterized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,283,1911,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,283,1911,1936]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="320">Drycothaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follow (translated): “Mesoventrite with tubercle; prothorax with lateral spine; scape without cicatrix at apex; pronotum without evident tubercles; elytra convex, without longitudinal carina and not depressed near suture.”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
In April the following year 
<bibRefCitation box="[505,793,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5098" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1991) Revisao da tribo Calliini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Giornali Italiano di Entomologia, 5, 243 - 262." type="journal article">Galileo &amp; Martins (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, proposed some transferences and synonymies, adding 
<taxonomicName authority="(Breuning, 1974)" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">D. mexicana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[280,465,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref4964" refString="Breuning, S. (1974) Neue Artenund Gattungen von Lamiinen (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Mitteilungenausdem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 50 (1), 149 - 165. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19590350108" type="journal article">Breuning, 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(originally 
<emphasis box="[621,889,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
Thrychestola 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[782,889,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) to this genus. Although the synonymy was formally made by 
<bibRefCitation box="[359,652,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5098" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1991) Revisao da tribo Calliini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Giornali Italiano di Entomologia, 5, 243 - 262." type="journal article">Galileo &amp; Martins (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, it was done so based on personal communication with Dr. Gérard L. Tavakilian 
<collectionCode box="[278,364,261,284]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">MNHN</collectionCode>
(Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle) who listed the same name as a new combination on August of the same year (
<bibRefCitation box="[440,634,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5706" refString="Tavakilian, G. L. (1991) Notas sinonimicas e novas combinacoes em longicorneos sul americanos (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 35 (2), 439 - 453." type="journal article">Tavakilian, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation box="[726,1015,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5139" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2010) Genero Drycothaea (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Chave para especies, nova combinacao, especies novas. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (5), 69 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000500001" type="journal article">Galileo &amp; Martins (2010)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1126,1268,297,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis box="[1126,1268,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">D. mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a key to the species of the continental America (which excludes the Antillian species) at alternative of couplet “10” (translated): “Pubescence of head, pronotum, and basal area of elytra yellowish, remarkably contrasting with darkbrown remaining pubescence of elytra.” The photography of the 
<typeStatus box="[897,995,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[1037,1174,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
T. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1067,1174,405,428]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">mexicana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1191,1318,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16. 10–13" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[172,1402,193,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[172,1402,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. 10–13, Drycothaea indivisa sp. nov., holotype, male: 10, dorsal view; 11, ventral view; 12, lateral view; 13, frontal view. 14–16, Drycothaea mexicana Breuning, 1974, holotype: 14, labels; 15, dorsal view; 16, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457796/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">Figs 14-16</figureCitation>
), revealed that 
<bibRefCitation box="[200,482,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5098" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1991) Revisao da tribo Calliini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Giornali Italiano di Entomologia, 5, 243 - 262." type="journal article">Galileo &amp; Martins (1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[494,552,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5139" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2010) Genero Drycothaea (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Chave para especies, nova combinacao, especies novas. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (5), 69 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000500001" type="journal article">2010</bibRefCitation>
) erroneously identified a specimen (a new species described herein) deposited at 
<collectionCode box="[179,252,476,500]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">MZSP</collectionCode>
as being 
<emphasis box="[361,512,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[361,508,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">D. mexicana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Besides other differences, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[818,960,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis box="[818,960,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">D. mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has uniform yellowish pubescence on the head, pronotum and base of the elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="321" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
Through the study of the tarsal claws of the holotype, it was also possible to confirm that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[1208,1350,549,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis box="[1208,1350,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">D. mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is truly a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="2016" box="[170,254,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Calliini">Calliini</taxonomicName>
and belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[431,563,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,563,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">Drycothaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">
Below, we are describing the specimen erroneously referred to as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[956,1100,621,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Drycothaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicana">
<emphasis box="[956,1100,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="321">D. mexicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1145,1431,620,645]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5098" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (1991) Revisao da tribo Calliini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Giornali Italiano di Entomologia, 5, 243 - 262." type="journal article">Martins &amp; Galileo (1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,212,656,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="321" refId="ref5139" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2010) Genero Drycothaea (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae): Chave para especies, nova combinacao, especies novas. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 50 (5), 69 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492010000500001" type="journal article">2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
